The paper deals with a problem in code-based cryptography, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The problem studied is related to decoding syndromes, which is a common task in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves algorithmic analysis and parameter selection, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the relative difficulty of ternary and binary syndrome decoding, which could have implications for security and information theory (cs.SI).
